parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without warning
and may not respond to braking. The accelerator pedal may stick or feel spongy
and the vehicle may lurch or surge forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the electronic throttle sensor can cause unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit sudden acceleration
hesitation
or stalling
and the check engine light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may not respond to braking or may accelerate unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
brakes do not engage or respond slowly
brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle accelerates instead of slowing down
sudden loss of brake pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: ABS system engages unnecessarily
brakes pulse or vibrate
vehicle accelerates instead of slowing down
sudden loss of brake pressure
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause brake failure, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
brake pedal goes to the floor
brakes do not engage or respond slowly
sudden loss of brake pressure
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Stripped Head Bolts and Head Gasket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head bolts and head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, coolant loss, and potentially a blown engine.
symptoms: The engine overheats
coolant leaks
the head gasket blows
and the engine stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Sludge and Coolant Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The buildup of oil sludge can cause engine damage, overheating, and coolant leaks, leading to engine failure.
symptoms: The engine overheats
coolant leaks
oil sludge buildup
and the engine stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and rough idling can cause accidents, especially when driving in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls or rough idles
especially when cold or after warming up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, especially when driving in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalyst and charcoal canister can cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests and potentially lead to engine damage.
symptoms: The vehicle fails emissions tests
and the catalyst and charcoal canister need to be replaced.
